communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Acholi is an ethnic group in Northern Uganda (an area commonly referred to as Acholiland, composed of the districts of Agago (78), Amuru (39), Gulu (17), Kitgum (42), Lamwo (97), Nwoya (107), and Pader (68) [numbered in the map below] and South Sudan (Magwe County).

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Uganda can be seen at http://healthmap.org/r/45kA. A map showing Acholiland can be seen at http://tinyurl.com/cx798ct. The current districts that compose the region (numbered above) can be seen at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Districts_of_Uganda.

The news item above is -- epidemiologically -- rather blurred, describing a concerning situation with regard to animal health. It includes suspicions of infectious diseases in several animal species (cattle, pigs, goats) while mentioning specifically FMD, CBPP, and ASF.

First-hand veterinary information is urgently needed from official national or international authorities, or from reliable, politically independent, professionally equipped NGOs.

The death of goats in Agoro sub-county and the description from Potika village in Agoro of a lethal cattle disease which "starts by losing appetite and feeling weak with diarrhoea," illustrates the need to exclude other pathogens, including morbillivirus. - Mod.AS]
